Description: Upper body sherd of Aeolian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; interior: glazed streaky black; exterior, from top: two lines; part of pendant roundel, swastika and part of undetermined motif as filling ornament.
Producer name: Made by: The London Dinos Group
Curator's comments: Probably from same dinos as 1924,1201.1026 and 1032.
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 252, no. 398)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.33)
